er Feeds\",\n107 |     perfMetric: \"94.2% Disruption Mitigation\",\n108 |     systemPrompt: \"Evaluate logistical alternatives strictly under margin safety bounds. Draft SAP transaction updates with approval seals.\",\n109 |     sandboxResponse: [\n110 |       {\n111 |         prompt: \"Simulate impact of Rotterdam harbor delays.\",\n112 |         answer: \"[KAFKA INGESTION ACTIVE - 3 ACTIVE ALERTS]\\n[SIMULATING SCENARIO: Rotterdam Transit Delay +48 hrs]\\n\\nScenario Results:\\n- Shipments Impacted: 3 containers of catalyst.\\n- Plant Impact: Inventory at Dusseldorf will drop below safety reserve in 14 hours.\\n- Mitigating Action: Redirect to Antwerp depot.\\n\\nAction: TRANSACTION PREPPED (Pending SAP Commit).\"\n113 |       }\n114 |     ]\n115 |   },\n116 |   {\n117 |     id: \"zero-trust-pii-guard\",\n118 |     name: \"Zero-Trust Sovereign PII Guard\",\n119 |     category: \"Compliance Agents\",\n120 |     desc: \"Inspects agent system calls, sanitizes outbound telemetry, dynamically masks sensitive personal data, and intercepts potential prompt-injection patterns.\",\n121 |     useCase: \"Real-time automated sanitization of agent query streams in regulated sectors.\",\n122 |     gffFit: \"Factory\",\n123 |     relatedCapabilities: [\"eBPF Interception\", \"Dynamic Entity Masking\", \"Policy Auditing\"],\n124 |     industry: \"Cross-Industry\",\n125 |     function: \"Information Security\",\n126 |     maturityStage: \"Production-Ready\",\n127 |     platformFit: \"On-Premises\",\n128 |     stages: [\"eBPF Intercept\", \"Dynamic Redaction Filter\", \"Policy Engine Match\", \"Sanitized Gateway\"],\n129 |     datasources: \"HashiCorp Vault Secrets, GFF Gateway Logs, Kubernetes ConfigMaps\",\n130 |     perfMetric: \"<8ms Interception Latency\",\n131 |     systemPrompt: \"Intercept and redact SSNs, banking credentials, and private keys. Throw exceptions if safety policies are breached.\",\n132 |     sandboxResponse: [\n133 |       {\n134 |         prompt: \"Ingest prompt containing SSN: 000-12-3456.\",\n135 |         answer: \"[eBPF LAYER DETECTED SENSITIVE INFO]\\n[REDACTION EXECUTED]\\n\\nInbound prompt sanitized:\\n- SSN: [REDACTED_SSN_MASK_001]\\n\\nClean stream dispatched to core language model.\"\n136 |       }\n137 |     ]\n138 |   },\n139 |   {\n140 |     id: \"personalized-cx-broker\",\n141 |     name: \"Hyper-Personalized CX Broker\",\n142 |     category: \"Customer Experience Agents\",\n143 |     desc: \"Classifies customer intent markers, orchestrates personalized resolutions, and drafts highly accurate, policy-approved drafts for service desks.\",\n144 |     useCase: \"Multi-channel B2C customer service resolution and automated ticket processing.\",\n145 |     gffFit: \"Foundry\",\n146 |     relatedCapabilities: [\"Intent Multi-Classification\", \"Persona Adaptation\", \"Human-in-the-Loop Gate\"],\n147 |     industry: \"Retail & E-Commerce\",\n148 |     function: \"Customer Service\",\n149 |     maturityStage: \"Production-Ready\",\n150 |     platformFit: \"Hybrid Cloud\",\n151 |     stages: [\"Omnichannel Hook\", \"Intent Classifier\", \"Knowledge Fetch\", \"Human Gate Route\"],\n152 |     datasources: \"Zendesk Webhooks, Salesforce CRM, Braze Messaging Hub\",\n153 |     perfMetric: \"84.5% Automated Resolution Rate\",\n154 |     systemPrompt: \"Address customer inquiries while strictly enforcing return policy parameters. Never exceed validated invoice thresholds.\",\n155 |     sandboxResponse: [\n156 |       {\n157 |         prompt: \"Inbound ticket: 'I ordered a GFF-Node-V2 and it arrived cracked.'\",\n158 |         answer: \"[INTENT CLASSIFIER: Damaged Item / Replacement Request]\\n[RETURNS POLICY CHECK: Valid within 30 days]\\n\\nDraft Resolution:\\n'Hello. We are sorry to hear your node was damaged in transit. You are fully eligible for a priority replacement at zero additional cost.'\\n\\n[HUMAN GATEWAY ENFORCED] Sent to success desk for review.\"\n159 |       }\n160 |     ]\n161 |   },\n162 |   {\n163 |     id: \"scenario-modeler-agent\",\n164 |     name: \"Scenario Modeler & Corporate Risk Agent\",\n165 |     category: \"Executive Agents\",\n166 |     desc: \"Performs strategic board-level strategic risk simulations, aggregates multi-departmental financial forecasts, and structures secure briefing reports.\",\n167 |     useCase: \"Simulating market variance projections and writing board-level decision reports.\",\n168 |     gffFit: \"Garage\",\n169 |     relatedCapabilities: [\"Monte Carlo Aggregation\", \"Macro-Economic Synthesis\", \"Briefing Compilation\"],\n170 |     industry: \"Cross-Industry\",\n171 |     function: \"Executive Strategy\",\n172 |     maturityStage: \"Pilot Active\",\n173 |     platformFit: \"Sovereign Stack\",\n174 |     stages: [\"Snowflake Ingestion\", \"Risk Modeler Engine\", \"Summarizer Node\", \"Sovereign PDF Compile\"],\n175 |     datasources: \"Snowflake Data Warehouse, General Ledger, Macro Feeds\",\n176 |     perfMetric: \"99.5% Trend Projection Matching\",\n177 |     systemPrompt: \"Simulate macro-economic scenarios. Restrict focus to liquidity ratios and capital reserves. Include confidence metrics.\",\n178 |     sandboxResponse: [\n179 |       {\n180 |         prompt: \"Simulate a 15% increase in commodity procurement costs.\",\n181 |         answer: \"[RUNNING MONTE CARLO SIMULATION: 10,000 iterations]\\n\\nSimulation Results under 1 surge:\\n- Net Margin Impact: -2.4% EBITDA across Manufacturing.\\n- Capital Reserves: Liquidity ratio decreases from 2.1 to 1.85.\\n\\nConfidence: 94% | Report prepped: executive-commodity-impact.pdf\"\n182 |       }\n183 |     ]\n184 |   },\n185 |   {\n186 |     id: \"multi-format-doc-analyzer\",\n187 |     name: \"Multi-Format Technical Document Analyzer\",\n188 |     category: \"Document Intelligence Agents\",\n189 |     desc: \"Parses complex technical engineering diagrams, SOX spreadsheets, and CAD schematics, aligning structural layout patterns with technical specifications.\",\n190 |     useCase: \"Extracting metadata and compliance flags from complex engineering design blueprints.\",\n191 |     gffFit: \"Foundry\",\n192 |     relatedCapabilities: [\"Hierarchical Blueprint Reading\", \"Engineering Spec Extraction\", \"CAD-Reference Mapping\"],\n193 |     industry: \"Energy & Utilities\",\n194 |     function: \"Engineering Operations\",\n195 |     maturityStage: \"Production-Ready\",\n196 |     platformFit: \"On-Premises\",\n197 |     stages: [\"S3 CAD Inbound\", \"Layout Parser\", \"Structural Extraction\", \"Spec Reconciliation\"],\n198 |     datasources: \"S3 Document Bucket, Engineering Spec Database, PLM Repository\",\n199 |     perfMetric: \"97.9% Key-Value Extraction Accuracy\",\n200 |     systemPrompt: \"Extract operational limits from technical diagrams. Flag any structural variances that deviate from GFF tolerances.\",\n201 |     sandboxResponse: [\n202 |       {\n203 |         prompt: \"Analyze CAD Spec Sheet: GFF-Turbine-V4.pdf.\",\n204 |         answer: \"[INGESTING S3 METADATA... OK]\\n[RUNNING LAYOUT PARSER]\\n\\nExtracted Parameters:\\n- Rotor Diameter: 14.2m (Complies with Spec)\\n- Core Operating Temperature: Up to 410C (WARNING: Exceeds standard GFF thermal guideline of 395C by 15C).\\n\\nThermal tolerance deviation has been logged.\"\n205 |       }\n206 |     ]\n207 |   },\n208 |   {\n209 |     id: \"freight-audit-agent\",\n210 |     name: \"Global Freight Audit Agent\",\n211 |     category: \"Procurement Agents\",\n212 |     desc: \"Audits high-volume carrier bills of lading against rate cards, identifies tariff discrepancies, and drafts dispute filings automatically.\",\n213 |     useCase: \"Continuous automated carrier invoice reconciliation and freight dispute resolution.\",\n214 |     gffFit: \"Factory\",\n215 |     relatedCapabilities: [\"Invoice Reconciliation\", \"Tariff Matching\", \"Dispute Resolution Engine\"],\n216 |     industry: \"Logistics & Transport\",\n217 |     function: \"Procurement & Sourcing\",\n218 |     maturityStage: \"Production-Ready\",\n219 |     platformFit: \"Sovereign Stack\",\n220 |     stages: [\"Invoice Parser\", \"BOL Cross-Check\", \"Tariff Verifier\", \"Payment Dispatcher\"],\n221 |     datasources: \"Carrier Logistics Portals, TMS Database, Tariff Agreement Repositories\",\n222 |     perfMetric: \"100% Rate Error Identification Rate\",\n223 |     systemPrompt: \"Compare bill of lading charges against approved contract tariff sheets. Initiate dispute files for discrepancies exceeding $10.\",\n224 |     sandboxResponse: [\n225 |       {\n226 |         prompt: \"Audit carrier invoice: INV-99214-Oceanic.csv.\",\n227 |         answer: \"[INGESTING OCEANIC INVOICE LINES... OK]\\n[CROSS-REFERENCING RATES AGAINST TARIFFS]\\n\\nAudit Results:\\n- Total Invoices Audited: 42 lines\\n- Error Found: Line #18 (Fuel Surcharge) matches at 14.5% ($1,850). Approved rate card limits fuel surcharge to 12% ($1,531).\\n\\nAction: Flagged $319 overcharge. Dispute letter prepped.\"\n228 |       }\n229 |     ]\n230 |   },\n231 |   {\n232 |     id: \"talent-alignment-planner\",\n233 |     name: \"Talent Alignment & Org Planner\",\n234 |     category: \"HR Agents\",\n235 |     desc: \"Maps anonymized employee profiles and professional credentials to internal capability gaps, prioritizing talent mobility in full data privacy.\",\n236 |     useCase: \"Internal talent matching, career pathing, and privacy-preserving org design.\",\n237 |     gffFit: \"Garage\",\n238 |     relatedCapabilities: [\"Skill Ontology Mapping\", \"Internal Mobility Matching\", \"Privacy-Preserving Semantics\"],\n239 |     industry: \"Cross-Industry\",\n240 |     function: \"Human Resources\",\n241 |     maturityStage: \"Pilot Active\",\n242 |     platformFit: \"On-Premises\",\n243 |     stages: [\"Anonymize Profiles\", \"Ontology Alignment\", \"Opportunity Matcher\", \"Advisory Compiler\"],\n244 |     datasources: \"Workday HCM, Internal Skill Matrices, Learning Management Systems\",\n245 |     perfMetric: \"3.2x Internal Talent Mobility Uplift\",\n246 |     systemPrompt: \"Analyze career trajectories and internal credentials in an anonymized sandbox. Avoid references to demographics.\",\n247 |     sandboxResponse: [\n248 |       {\n249 |         prompt: \"Find candidate profiles suited for Senior AI opening.\",\n250 |         answer: \"[SCANNING SKILL MATRICES: Anonymized Profile Pool]\\n\\nTop Matches Found:\\n1. Profile ID: #ANON-99021 (Alignment: 94% - matches lead Next.js framework qualifications and GFF Certs).\\n\\nRecommendations compiled in secure portal.\"\n251 |       }\n252 |     ]\n253 |   }\n254 | ];\n255 | \n256 | \n257 | \n258 | export default function BuildMarketplacePage() {\n259 |   // State variables\n260 |   const [activeTab, setActiveTab] = useState<string>(\"All Patterns\");\n261 |   const [industryFilter, setIndustryFilter] = useState<string>(\"All Industries\");\n262 |   const [functionFilter, setFunctionFilter] = useState<string>(\"All Functions\");\n263 |   const [maturityFilter, setMaturityFilter] = useState<string>(\"All Stages\");\n264 |   const [platformFilter, setPlatformFilter] = useState<string>(\"All Fits\");\n265 |   const [searchQuery, setSearchQuery] = useState<string>(\"\");\n266 | \n267 |   const [compareIds, setCompareIds] = useState<string[]>([]);\n268 |   const [isCompareOpen, setIsCompareOpen] = useState<boolean>(false);\n269 | \n270 |   const [sandboxId, setSandboxId] = useState<string | null>(null);\n271 |   const [sandboxLogs, setSandboxLogs] = useState<string[]>([]);\n272 |   const [sandboxInput, setSandboxInput] = useState<string>(\"\");\n273 |   const [sandboxIsBooting, setSandboxIsBooting] = useState<boolean>(false);\n274 |   const [sandboxIsSuccess, setSandboxIsSuccess] = useState<boolean>(false);\n275 |   \n276 |   const [chatId, setChatId] = useState<string | null>(null);\n277 |   const [chatMessages, setChatMessages] = useState<Array<{ sender: \"user\" | \"agent\"; text: string }>>([]);\n278 |   const [chatInput, setChatInput] = useState<string>(\"\");\n279 | \n280 |   const terminalEndRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);\n281 |   const chatEndRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);\n282 | \n283 |   const totalCertifiedCount = BLUEPRINTS.length;\n284 |   const prodReadyCount = BLUEPRINTS.filter(b => b.maturityStage === \"Production-Ready\").length;\n285 | \n286 | \n287 |   // Computed variables and filtering\n288 |   const filteredBlueprints = useMemo(() => {\n289 |     return BLUEPRINTS.filter((bp) => {\n290 |       if (activeTab !== \"All Patterns\" && bp.category !== activeTab) return false;\n291 |       if (industryFilter !== \"All Industries\" && bp.industry !== industryFilter) return false;\n292 |       if (functionFilter !== \"All Functions\" && bp.function !== functionFilter) return false;\n293 |       if (maturityFilter !== \"All Stages\" && bp.maturityStage !== maturityFilter) return false;\n294 |       if (platformFilter !== \"All Fits\" && bp.platformFit !== platformFilter) return false;\n295 | \n296 |       if (searchQuery.trim() !== \"\") {\n297 |         const query = searchQuery.toLowerCase();\n298 |         const matchesName = bp.name.toLowerCase().includes(query);\n299 |         const matchesDesc = bp.desc.toLowerCase().includes(query);\n300 |         const matchesUseCase = bp.useCase.toLowerCase().includes(query);\n301 |         const matchesCapabilities = bp.relatedCapabilities.some((cap) => cap.toLowerCase().includes(query));\n302 |         return matchesName || matchesDesc || matchesUseCase || matchesCapabilities;\n303 |       }\n304 | \n305 |       return true;\n306 |     });\n307 |   }, [activeTab, industryFilter, functionFilter, maturityFilter, platformFilter, searchQuery]);\n308 | \n309 |   const isFilterActive = useMemo(() => {\n310 |     return (\n311 |       activeTab !== \"All Patterns\" ||\n312 |       industryFilter !== \"All Industries\" ||\n313 |       functionFilter !== \"All Functions\" ||\n314 |       maturityFilter !== \"All Stages\" ||\n315 |       platformFilter !== \"All Fits\" ||\n316 |       searchQuery !== \"\"\n317 |     );\n318 |   }, [activeTab, industryFilter, functionFilter, maturityFilter, platformFilter, searchQuery]);\n319 | \n320 |   const resetAllFilters = () => {\n321 |     setActiveTab(\"All Patterns\");\n322 |     setIndustryFilter(\"All Industries\");\n323 |     setFunctionFilter(\"All Functions\");\n324 |     setMaturityFilter(\"All Stages\");\n325 |     setPlatformFilter(\"All Fits\");\n326 |     setSearchQuery(\"\");\n327 |   };\n328 | \n329 |   const comparedAgents = useMemo(() => {\n330 |     return BLUEPRINTS.filter((bp) => compareIds.includes(bp.id));\n331 |   }, [compareIds]);\n332 | \n333 | \n334 |   // Core handlers\n335 |   const toggleCompare = (id: string) => {\n336 |     if (compareIds.includes(id)) {\n337 |       setCompareIds((prev) => prev.filter((item) => item !== id));\n338 |     } else {\n339 |       if (compareIds.length >= 3) {\n340 |         alert(\"Maximum comparison limit reached. Please remove an agent before adding another.\");\n341 |         return;\n342 |       }\n343 |       setCompareIds((prev) => [...prev, id]);\n344 |     }\n345 |   };\n346 | \n347 |   const clearComparison = () => {\n348 |     setCompareIds([]);\n349 |     setIsCompareOpen(false);\n350 |   };\n351 | \n352 |   useEffect(() => {\n353 |     if (terminalEndRef.current) {\n354 |       terminalEndRef.current.scrollIntoView({ behavior: \"smooth\" });\n355 |     }\n356 |   }, [sandboxLogs, sandboxIsBooting]);\n357 | \n358 |   useEffect(() => {\n359 |     if (chatEndRef.current) {\n360 |       chatEndRef.current.scrollIntoView({ behavior: \"smooth\" });\n361 |     }\n362 |   }, [chatMessages]);\n363 | \n364 |   const handleOpenSandbox = (id: string) => {\n365 |     const bp = BLUEPRINTS.find((b) => b.id === id);\n366 |     if (!bp) return;\n367 | \n368 |     setSandboxId(id);\n369 |     setSandboxIsBooting(true);\n370 |     setSandboxIsSuccess(false);\n371 |     setSandboxLogs([]);\n372 |     setSandboxInput(\"\");\n373 | \n374 |     const bootLogs = [\n375 |       `Initializing secure OCI container for ${bp.id}_v1.0...`,\n376 |       `Enforcing Context Boundary Spec (VPC: isolated-gff, RAM: 16GB, GPU Allocation: 2x Nvidia H100)...`,\n377 |       `Activating Safety Redaction filters (Zero-Trust eBPF Packet Inspector)...`,\n378 |       `Establishing cryptographic connections to local adapters: [${bp.datasources}]...`,\n379 |       `Injecting Sovereign System Directives into local context pipeline...`,\n380 |       `[SUCCESS] Safe containment boundaries established. Sandbox online.`\n381 |     ];\n382 | \n383 |     let timer = 0;\n384 |     bootLogs.forEach((log, index) => {\n385 |       setTimeout(() => {\n386 |         setSandboxLogs((prev) => [...prev, `> ${log}`]);\n387 |         if (index === bootLogs.length - 1) {\n388 |           setSandboxIsBooting(false);\n389 |           setSandboxIsSuccess(true);\n390 |         }\n391 |       }, timer);\n392 |       timer += 400;\n393 |     });\n394 |   };\n395 | \n396 |   const handleSandboxSubmit = (e?: React.FormEvent) => {\n397 |     if (e) e.preventDefault();\n398 |     if (!sandboxInput.trim() || !sandboxId) return;\n399 | \n400 |     const bp = BLUEPRINTS.find((b) => b.id === sandboxId);\n401 |     if (!bp) return;\n402 | \n403 |     const userPrompt = sandboxInput;\n404 |     setSandboxLogs((prev) => [...prev, `$ ${userPrompt}`]);\n405 |     setSandboxInput(\"\");\n406 | \n407 |     setTimeout(() => {\n408 |       const matchedQA = bp.sandboxResponse.find(\n409 |         (qa) => qa.prompt.toLowerCase().includes(userPrompt.toLowerCase()) || \n410 |                 userPrompt.toLowerCase().includes(qa.prompt.toLowerCase())\n411 |       );\n412 | \n413 |       if (matchedQA) {\n414 |         setSandboxLogs((prev) => [...prev, matchedQA.answer]);\n415 |       } else {\n416 |         setSandboxLogs((prev) => [\n417 |           ...prev, \n418 |           `[EVALUATING SEMANTIC GRAPH VECTOR... OK]\\n[MATCH CRITERIA MET WITH LOW THRESHOLD]\\n\\nReceived: \"${userPrompt}\"\\n\\n[COMPLIANCE GATE NOTICE] Standard safety instruction intercepts any raw query not predefined inside this demo terminal. To execute custom queries, deploy this blueprint inside GFF Foundry Studio or consult with an integration engineer.\\n\\nSovereign System Directives are active: Zero risk of data leaks.`\n419 |         ]);\n420 |       }\n421 |     }, 800);\n422 |   };\n423 | \n424 |   const handlePresetSandboxQuery = (queryText: string) => {\n425 |     setSandboxInput(queryText);\n426 |     setTimeout(() => {\n427 |       setSandboxLogs((prev) => [...prev, `$ ${queryText}`]);\n428 |       setSandboxInput(\"\");\n429 |       const bp = BLUEPRINTS.find((b) => b.id === sandboxId);\n430 |       if (!bp) return;\n431 |       const matchedQA = bp.sandboxResponse.find((qa) => qa.prompt === queryText);\n432 |       if (matchedQA) {\n433 |         setSandboxLogs((prev) => [...prev, matchedQA.answer]);\n434 |       }\n435 |     }, 200);\n436 |   };\n437 | \n438 |   const handleOpenChat = (id: string) => {\n439 |     const bp = BLUEPRINTS.find((b) => b.id === id);\n440 |     if (!bp) return;\n441 | \n442 |     setChatId(id);\n443 |     setChatInput(\"\");\n444 |     setChatMessages([\n445 |       {\n446 |         sender: \"agent\",\n447 |         text: `Secure connection established with ${bp.name} (ID: ${bp.id}_v1.0). I am running within a sovereign execution enclave. How can I assist you with your integration blueprint or structural architecture today?`\n448 |       }\n449 |     ]);\n450 |   };\n451 | \n452 |   const handleChatSubmit = (e?: React.FormEvent) => {\n453 |     if (e) e.preventDefault();\n454 |     if (!chatInput.trim() || !chatId) return;\n455 | \n456 |     const userMsg = chatInput;\n457 |     setChatMessages((prev) => [...prev, { sender: \"user\", text: userMsg }]);\n458 |     setChatInput(\"\");\n459 | \n460 |     setTimeout(() => {\n461 |       setChatMessages((prev) => [\n462 |         ...prev,\n463 |         {\n464 |           sender: \"agent\",\n465 |           text: `Understood. Your inquiry regarding \"${userMsg}\" relates directly to GFF ${\n466 |             BLUEPRINTS.find((b) => b.id === chatId)?.gffFit\n467 |           } deployment guidelines. Every transaction is governed by strict local context constraints. For detailed topology maps and integration templates, let's schedule a dedicated GFF Systems Engineer Sync.`\n468 |         }\n469 |       ]);\n470 |     }, 600);\n471 |   };\n472 | \n473 | \n474 |   return (\n475 |     <InnerPageShell>\n476 |       {/* Background Dots */}\n477 |       <div className=\"absolute inset-0 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_center,rgba(255,255,255,0.02)_1px,transparent_1px)] bg-[size:24px_24px] pointer-events-none\" />\n478 | \n479 |       <InnerPageHero\n480 |         category=\"Sovereign Assets\"\n481 |         title=\"Agent Blueprint Registry and Architecture Catalog\"\n482 |         highlightedWord=\"Registry\"\n483 |         highlightColor=\"blue\"\n484 |         description=\"Explore GFF's catalog of certified multi-agent patterns, workflows, and accelerators. Every blueprint is pre-engineered with strict input/output boundaries, static integration boundaries, and dedicated safety enclaves for secure, localized execution.\"\n485 |         breadcrumbs={[\n486 |           { label: \"Build Suite\", href: \"/build\" },\n487 |           { label: \"Blueprint Registry\" }\n488 |         ]}\n489 |       />\n490 | \n491 |       {/* REGISTRY TELEMETRY BANNERS */}\n492 |       <div className=\"max-w-[1795px] mx-auto px-6 lg:px-16 -mt-8 mb-16\">\n493 |         <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6 bg-[#040405] border border-white/5 rounded-2xl p-6 relative overflow-hidden\">\n494 |           <div className=\"absolute top-0 right-0 w-[20%] h-[100%] bg-gradient-to-l from-blue-500/5 to-transparent blur-[40px] pointer-events-none\" />\n495 |           \n496 |           <div className=\"space-y-1\">\n497 |             <span className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-white/40 uppercase tracking-widest font-bold\">BLUEPRINTS ACTIVE</span>\n498 |             <div className=\"flex items-baseline gap-2\">\n499 |               <span className=\"text-3xl font-bold text-white font-mono\">{totalCertifiedCount}</span>\n500 |               <span className=\"text-[10px] text-green-400 font-mono flex items-center gap-0.5\">\n501 |                 <CheckCircle2 className=\"w-3 h-3 inline\" /> CERTIFIED\n502 |               </span>\n503 |             </div>\n504 |             <p className=\"text-xs text-white/50 font-light\">Verified sovereign standards</p>\n505 |           </div>\n506 | \n507 |           <div className=\"space-y-1 border-t sm:border-t-0 sm:border-l border-white/5 pt-4 sm:pt-0 sm:pl-6\">\n508 |             <span className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-white/40 uppercase tracking-widest font-bold\">DEPLOYMENT BASELINE</span>\n509 |             <div className=\"flex items-baseline gap-2\">\n510 |               <span className=\"text-3xl font-bold text-[#009DFF] font-mono\">OCI</span>\n511 |               <span className=\"text-[11px] text-white/70 font-mono font-semibold\">Containerized</span>\n512 |             </div>\n513 |             <p className=\"text-xs text-white/50 font-light\">Air-gapped VPC enclaves</p>\n514 |           </div>\n515 | \n516 |           <div className=\"space-y-1 border-t lg:border-t-0 lg:border-l border-white/5 pt-4 lg:pt-0 lg:pl-6\">\n517 |             <span className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-white/40 uppercase tracking-widest font-bold\">PRODUCTION READY</span>\n518 |             <div className=\"flex items-baseline gap-2\">\n519 |               <span className=\"text-3xl font-bold text-white font-mono\">{prodReadyCount}</span>\n520 |               <span className=\"text-[11px] text-white/50 font-semibold\">/ {totalCertifiedCount} Ready</span>\n521 |             </div>\n522 |             <p className=\"text-xs text-white/50 font