{"ts":"2026-06-26T22:10:27.124Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Refining the Modal Specs**\n\nI'm making progress on editing the Comparative Specifications Modal. Currently, I'm integrating `<AnimatePresence>` to manage the modal's entry and exit animations. I'm focusing on wrapping `{isCompareOpen && ...}` within it. Furthermore, the outer element will use a `<motion.div>` with `initial={{ opacity: 0 }}`.\n\n\n**Enhancing the Modal Animation**\n\nI've been working on the entry animation for the inner modal container. I've implemented a `<motion.div>` with a scale and fade-in effect to provide a more polished appearance. The `initial`, `animate`, and `exit` properties are configured with specific durations and easing functions for optimal responsiveness. I'm aiming for a subtle yet impactful visual enhancement.\n\n\n**Finalizing the Modal Structure**\n\nI'm now focusing on the modal's internal components, specifically the title bar and the table header. The title bar's styling is set, and I'm adding a close button with an `X` icon. The table header is dynamically populated with agent names. I'm leveraging `comparedAgents.map` for the latter. I'm aiming for a clean, informative, and functional header.\n\n\n**Structuring the Table Header**\n\nI'm currently working on the table's header and body structure within the Comparative Specifications Modal. I've focused on styling and data integration. I'm dynamically populating the table header with agent names from `comparedAgents`, which are mapped to render. The table body rows are built, including a GFF Framework Tier and Use Case Focus. I'm focusing on text and styling for the agent data to improve clarity.\n\n\n**Refining Data Display**\n\nI'm now integrating agent data into table cells within the modal. I'm focusing on displaying agent use cases, target scope (industry and function), and system prompts. For the target scope, I'm structuring industry and function in a readable format using `<strong>` tags. I'm aiming for clarity in these specific data renderings.\n\n\n"}}
